The '''Kansas Building Science Institute''' is a [[vocational school]] located in [[Manhattan, Kansas]]. The Institute conducts week-long [http://www.resnet.us/rater/default.htm Home Energy Rater Trainings] (HERS) as well as Building Performance Index (BPI) and Weatherization (WX) Trainings, among others.<ref>[http://www.kansasbuildingscience.com/classes.htm Class Overview] Kansas Building Science Institute, Retrieved 30 December 2009</ref>
==Training center== The Institute conducts trainings in a {{convert|3000|sqft|m2|adj=on}} multi-purpose classroom and training center in Manhattan. The campus also includes a [[furnace]] lab, a mobile home for Weatherization Trainings, and an attached house to perform test ratings and inspections on. Other houses around Manhattan are also used for this purpose.<ref>[http://www.kansasbuildingscience.com/who.htm Who we are] Kansas Building Science Institute, Retrieved 30 December 2009</ref>
